text: It's almost ironic to read this in 2023, but Skorzeny writes how in Nuremberg prison the Allies put black guards as a way to humiliate the German prisoners, but they were the only ones who "refused to treat them like animals" and smuggled him and others cigarettes and chocolate.
He was far from sensationalism and pseudo-moralistic "humanistic" aggrandizations, which makes the short remark in his autobiography quite sincere.
